\newlabel{tab:celeba_clip_all40_per_concept_ctrl}{{17}{44}{Per-concept mean control accuracy change $\Delta $Ctrl (\%) on CelebA, all 40 binary attributes. For each concept, $\Delta $Ctrl is averaged over the 5 least-correlated control attributes (closer to zero = more surgical). $\lambda ^*$ selection matches Table~\ref {tab:celeba_clip_all40_per_concept_leak}}{table.caption.39}{}}
\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {18}{\ignorespaces Geometry evidence map organizing the appendix diagnostics into four research blocks. Each block addresses a distinct aspect of manifold structure: subspace sufficiency examines whether task-relevant computation concentrates in a low-dimensional linear subspace, perturbation sensitivity tests whether on-manifold directions matter more than orthogonal directions, representation connectivity evaluates whether the manifold remains connected across domains, and multi-layer accumulation tracks error compounding through the network. These diagnostics support the mechanism discussion and motivate the need for manifold-aware erasure methods but do not by themselves establish causality.}}{44}{table.caption.40}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{tab:geometry_schedule}{{18}{44}{Geometry evidence map organizing the appendix diagnostics into four research blocks. Each block addresses a distinct aspect of manifold structure: subspace sufficiency examines whether task-relevant computation concentrates in a low-dimensional linear subspace, perturbation sensitivity tests whether on-manifold directions matter more than orthogonal directions, representation connectivity evaluates whether the manifold remains connected across domains, and multi-layer accumulation tracks error compounding through the network. These diagnostics support the mechanism discussion and motivate the need for manifold-aware erasure methods but do not by themselves establish causality}{table.caption.40}{}}
\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {19}{\ignorespaces \textbf  {Per-row $\lambda _i$ statistics for the proposed pipeline ($\varepsilon = 0.1$, $\lambda _{\max }=64$) on the 39-panel NLP grid at 50\%-depth.} Each cell averages the per-row $\lambda _i$ first across all 60 outer iterations of one trajectory, then across the 13 model panels of the concept. The within-panel $p_{10}/p_{90}$ spread (mean across panels) is roughly $14/45$, i.e.\ a $\sim $10$\times $ ratio between the least- and most-confident rows in a single iteration. The safety cap $\lambda _{\max }=64$ is observed only sporadically (max 57.32 across 39$\times $60 = 2340 iterations); the closed-form rule rarely binds against it.}}{45}{table.caption.50}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{tab:lambda_stats}{{19}{45}{\textbf {Per-row $\lambda _i$ statistics for the proposed pipeline ($\varepsilon = 0.1$, $\lambda _{\max }=64$) on the 39-panel NLP grid at 50\%-depth.} Each cell averages the per-row $\lambda _i$ first across all 60 outer iterations of one trajectory, then across the 13 model panels of the concept. The within-panel $p_{10}/p_{90}$ spread (mean across panels) is roughly $14/45$, i.e.\ a $\sim $10$\times $ ratio between the least- and most-confident rows in a single iteration. The safety cap $\lambda _{\max }=64$ is observed only sporadically (max 57.32 across 39$\times $60 = 2340 iterations); the closed-form rule rarely binds against it}{table.caption.50}{}}
\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {20}{\ignorespaces \textbf  {Per-panel breakdown.} Signed $(S-S_{\text  {floor}})$ in pp at the trajectory step closest to the per-panel majority-class floor, subject to $|\Delta Y| \le B$pp control-damage budget. Bold = best (smallest absolute deviation from floor) per panel per budget block. `--' = no in-budget step at that budget for that method. Final rows: per-budget per-method mean across the 39 panels and TanGCE{} W/T/L counts vs.\ the best other method (0.5pp tie band).}}{45}{table.caption.52}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{tab:per_panel_breakdown}{{20}{45}{\textbf {Per-panel breakdown.} Signed $(S-S_{\text {floor}})$ in pp at the trajectory step closest to the per-panel majority-class floor, subject to $|\Delta Y| \le B$pp control-damage budget. Bold = best (smallest absolute deviation from floor) per panel per budget block. `--' = no in-budget step at that budget for that method. Final rows: per-budget per-method mean across the 39 panels and \TanGCE {} W/T/L counts vs.\ the best other method (0.5pp tie band)}{table.caption.52}{}}
